
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class City {
    +String name
    +int inhabitants
}

class Attraction {
    +String name
    +String address
}

class GuidedTour {
    +int duration  // in minutes or hours
    +int tourNumber
    +int maxVisitors = 20
}

class Visitor {
    +String name
}

class Guide {
    +String name
}

class Discount {
    +double amount
}

' Relationships

City "1" -- "*" Attraction : has
GuidedTour "1" -- "*" Discount : may have
GuidedTour "1" -- "1" Guide : requires
GuidedTour "1" -- "*" Visitor : participates (max 20)
Visitor "1" -- "*" Discount : may receive

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **City** contains multiple **Attractions**.
- Each **GuidedTour** is associated with an **Attraction**, though this association wasn't explicitly mentioned but can be inferred from context.
- A **GuidedTour** has a **Guide** and can include up to 20 **Visitors**.
- **Discounts** are optional and can be applied to both **GuidedTours** and **Visitors**.

